{"id": "test-00191", "text": "LONDON 1996-12-06", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "LONDON"}]}
{"id": "test-00192", "text": "Centre Jason Little will miss Australia's end-of-tour fixture against the Barbarians at Twickenham on Saturday.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 7, "end": 19, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Jason Little"}, {"start": 30, "end": 39, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Australia"}, {"start": 74, "end": 84, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Barbarians"}, {"start": 88, "end": 98, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Twickenham"}]}
{"id": "test-00193", "text": "Little has opted not to risk aggravating the knee injury which ruled him out of a large chunk of the tour and is replaced by fellow Queenslander Daniel Herbert.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Little"}, {"start": 132, "end": 144, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Queenslander"}, {"start": 145, "end": 159, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Daniel Herbert"}]}
{"id": "test-00194", "text": "Owen Finegan has recovered from the knocks he took in last weekend's test against Wales and retains his place in the back-row ahead of Daniel Manu.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 12, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Owen Finegan"}, {"start": 82, "end": 87, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Wales"}, {"start": 135, "end": 146, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Daniel Manu"}]}
{"id": "test-00195", "text": "The Wallabies have their sights set on a 13th successive victory to end their European tour with a 100 percent record but also want to turn on the style and provide David Campese with a fitting send-off in his final match in Australian colours.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 4, "end": 13, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Wallabies"}, {"start": 78, "end": 86, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "European"}, {"start": 165, "end": 178, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "David Campese"}, {"start": 225, "end": 235, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Australian"}]}
{"id": "test-00196", "text": "The Wallabies currently have no plans to make any special presentation to the 34-year-old winger but a full house of 75,000 spectators will still gather in the hope of witnessing one last moment of magic.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 4, "end": 13, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Wallabies"}]}
{"id": "test-00197", "text": "Campese will be up against a familiar foe in the shape of Barbarians captain Rob Andrew, the man who kicked Australia to defeat with a last-ditch drop-goal in the World Cup quarter-final in Cape Town.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 7, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Campese"}, {"start": 58, "end": 68, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Barbarians"}, {"start": 77, "end": 87, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Rob Andrew"}, {"start": 108, "end": 117, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Australia"}, {"start": 163, "end": 172, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "World Cup"}, {"start": 190, "end": 199, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Cape Town"}]}
{"id": "test-00198", "text": "\"Campo has a massive following in this country and has had the public with him ever since he first played here in 1984, \"said Andrew, also likely to be making his final Twickenham appearance.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 1, "end": 6, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Campo"}, {"start": 126, "end": 132, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Andrew"}, {"start": 169, "end": 179, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Twickenham"}]}
{"id": "test-00199", "text": "On tour, Australia have won all four tests against Italy, Scotland, Ireland and Wales, and scored 414 points at an average of almost 35 points a game.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 9, "end": 18, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Australia"}, {"start": 51, "end": 56, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Italy"}, {"start": 58, "end": 66, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Scotland"}, {"start": 68, "end": 75, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Ireland"}, {"start": 80, "end": 85, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Wales"}]}
